* TODO
** fixed bug with alerts
** added character encodings on demand
Zotero preferences are used, so extensions.zotero.export.displayCharsetOption is always set to true and
extensions.zotero.export.translatorSettings is also modified from Lyz
This only means that, when exporting from Zotero, character encoding combo box is displayed.
In Lyz, the character encoding can be modified when creating new bibtex file or when updating bibtex.
** added BOM
** additional character mappings for cite keys
** Please note: update bibtex 
Update bibtex will only update current lyx document. 
Multiple document update is implemented, but seems unreliable. Needs more testing.
** citekeys now conform to /[^a-z0-9\!\$\&\*\+\-\.\/\:\;\<\>\?\[\]\^\_\`\|]+/g


